	<text xml:lang="en">
		<body>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head n="1">Introduction</head><p>We intended to provide a base line for the robust task at CLEF 2006. Our system applied to ad-hoc CLEF 2005 data <ref type="bibr" coords="1,91.08,488.92,73.07,8.96" target="#b1">(Hackl et al. 2005</ref>) is an adaptive fusion system based on the MIMOR model <ref type="bibr" coords="1,414.36,488.92,109.99,8.96;1,70.92,500.44,21.57,8.96" target="#b3">(Mandl &amp; Womser-Hacker 2004)</ref>. For the base line experiments, we solely optimized blind relevance feedback (BRF) parameters based on a strategy developed by Carpineto et al. <ref type="bibr" coords="1,225.12,511.96,88.67,8.96" target="#b0">(Carpineto et al. 2001)</ref>. The basic retrieval engine is Lucene.</p></div>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head n="2">System Setup</head><p>Two runs for the English and two for the French monolingual data were submitted. The results for both test and training topics are shown in table 1 and 2, respectively. Only the runs for French have reached a competitive level of above 0.2 MAP. The results for the geometric average for the English topics are worse, because low performance for several topics leads to a sharp drop in the performance according to this measure.</p></div>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head n="3">Future Work</head><p>For future experiments, we intend to exploit the knowledge on the impact of named entities on the retrieval process <ref type="bibr" coords="2,103.92,283.60,135.91,8.96">(Mandl &amp; Womser-Hacker 2005)</ref> as well as selective relevance feedback strategies in order to improve robustness <ref type="bibr" coords="2,115.56,295.12,47.58,8.96" target="#b2">(Kwok 2005</ref>).</p></div><figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="table" xml:id="tab_0" coords="1,142.20,612.09,300.37,85.47"><head>Table 1 .</head><label>1</label><figDesc>Results for Submitted Monolingual Runs</figDesc><table coords="1,142.20,629.32,300.37,68.24"><row><cell>Run</cell><cell cols="2">Language Stemming</cell><cell>BRF</cell><cell>GeoAve</cell><cell>MAP</cell></row><row><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell>(docs. -terms)</cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row><row><cell cols="2">uhienmo1 English</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>5-30</cell><cell>0.01%</cell><cell>7.98%</cell></row><row><cell cols="2">uhienmo2 English</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>15-30</cell><cell>0.01%</cell><cell>7.12%</cell></row><row><cell>uhifrmo1</cell><cell>French</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>5-30</cell><cell>5.76%</cell><cell>28.50%</cell></row><row><cell>uhifrmo2</cell><cell>French</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>15-30</cell><cell>6.25%</cell><cell>29.85%</cell></row></table></figure>
<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="table" xml:id="tab_1" coords="2,142.20,84.93,303.85,85.47"><head>Table 2 .</head><label>2</label><figDesc>Result for Training Topics for Submitted Monolingual Runs</figDesc><table coords="2,142.20,102.16,303.85,68.24"><row><cell>Run</cell><cell cols="2">Language Stemming</cell><cell>BRF</cell><cell>GeoAve</cell><cell>MAP</cell></row><row><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell>(docs. -terms)</cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row><row><cell cols="2">uhienmo1 English</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>5-30</cell><cell>0.01%</cell><cell>7.16%</cell></row><row><cell cols="2">uhienmo2 English</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>15-30</cell><cell>0.01%</cell><cell>6.33%</cell></row><row><cell>uhifrmo1</cell><cell>French</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>5-30</cell><cell>8.58%</cell><cell>25.26%</cell></row><row><cell>uhifrmo2</cell><cell>French</cell><cell>Lucene</cell><cell>15-30</cell><cell>9.88%</cell><cell>28.47%</cell></row></table></figure>
